quest.name: It's Not a Bug, It's a Creature
journal: The moogle expedition has run into an unexpected problem.
Monsters of unknown origin have burst forth from the eggs littering the ruins of Tharl Oom Khash. Slay them so the moogles can continue their expedition undisturbed.
The corpses of the beasts now lie among the ruins. Report to the glimpsing moogle.
The moogle thanks you for your bravery, excited that the expedition can get back on its way.

dialogue.name: GUIDEMOG01855
dialogue.text: We're all here for a bit of exploring, kupo!

dialogue.name: FIELDTRIPMOGA01856
dialogue.text: Hmm... How interesting! I'll share my findings with the others shortly, kupo.

dialogue.name: FIELDTRIPMOGB01857
dialogue.text: While we were exploring the ruins some vile monsters we've never seen before popped out of the eggs littering the area. They were sighted at three different locations around the ruinsâ”€dispatch them so the expedition can continue, kupo.

dialogue.name: FIELDTRIPMOGB01857
dialogue.text: I've never seen such horrific monstrosities. Make sure they don't interrupt our expedition.

dialogue.name: FIELDTRIPMOGA01856
dialogue.text: There's never a dull moment here. I'll have to let the others know what I've found soon, kupo.

dialogue.name: GUIDEMOG01855
dialogue.text: It's been quite an expedition, kupo!

dialogue.name: FIELDTRIPMOGA01856
dialogue.text: Truly fascinating! I must let the others know.

dialogue.name: FIELDTRIPMOGB01857
dialogue.text: Many thanks for ridding the ruins of those vile brutes, kupo! Now we can continue on with our expedition in earnest.
